{ Hey everyone in Chessable Land. I am GM Ben Finegold and this is my second Chessable course.  My first course concentrated on play from White's side, so, I thought for my next course I would give you people something to play with Black against 1.e4.  The course work this time is for Black playing the Sicilian Defense,  1.e4  c5  . I have played the Sicilian for over 30 years and wanted to share my knowledge in my favorite lines for Black. I chose almost all the lines based on my work in the opening over the last 30+ years of chess praxis.  The reason I play the Sicilian Defense in the first place is an interesting piece of trivia. I saw a game played between A. Ivanov and S. Rachels from 1989:   @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  c5  2.Nf3  Nc6  3.d4  cxd4  4.Nxd4  Nf6  5.Nc3  d6  6.Bg5  e6  7.Qd2  Be7  8.O-O-O  Nxd4  9.Qxd4  O-O  10.f4  Qa5  11.Bc4  Bd7  12.e5  dxe5  13.fxe5  Bc6  14.Bd2  Nd7  15.Nd5  Qd8  16.Nxe7+  Qxe7  17.Rhe1  Rfd8  18.Qg4  Nf8  19.Bd3  Rxd3  20.cxd3  Qd7  21.Re3  Qd5  22.Kb1  Ng6  23.Bc3  Qxg2  24.Qxg2  Bxg2  25.Rg3  Bc6  26.Rdg1  Rd8  27.Kc2  Rd7  28.b3  Kh8  29.Rg4  Ne7  30.Rd4  Bd5  31.Rf4  Nf5  32.Kd2  Bc6  33.a4  h6  34.Rxf5  exf5  35.Rxg7  Rxd3+  36.Kxd3  1/2-1/2   I always like a good exchange sacrifice and this line fascinated me. Over the years I decided to play differently in my own games, starting with  @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp3ppp/2nppn2/6B1/3NP3/2N5/PPPQ1PPP/R3KB1R b KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7...a6  , although  7...Be7  is still fine for Black.   I have had a lot of success over the years with the Sicilian and a lot of sharp and interesting games. This course is for all players from beginner to about 1800 FIDE. Of course, higher-rated players will enjoy learning the lines as well. It is especially for people who are looking for something new to play against 1.e4 and I know my fans will have success with the lines I recommend throughout the course.  Happy Checkmating! }
