[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5
{ The Sicilian! Black controls the d4-square, and keeps their center pawns @@StartBracket@@e7 and d7@@EndBracket@@ safe from capture.   In the Open Sicilian, where White plays d2-d4 early @@StartBracket@@move 3 or 4@@EndBracket@@, Black will capture the pawn and have 2 center pawns @@StartBracket@@e and d@@EndBracket@@ to White's one center pawn @@StartBracket@@e4@@EndBracket@@.   Playing the Sicilian shows that Black wants to fight for an advantage rather than playing the symmetrical  1...e5  and trying for equality.  In this Quickstarter Guide, you will find a couple of variations per chapter which I think demonstrate thematic play in each line. Getting a good grip on them should set you up for success.   Enjoy! }
2. Nf3
{ White's main move by far, aiming for an Open Sicilian. It's called that because after d4, Black's c-pawn and White's d-pawn are exchanged, opening some lines for active play. }
2... Nc6 3. Bb5
{ This has become quite popular over the last 20 years, and I face it almost as often as the Open Sicilian with  3.d4  . }
3... Nf6
{ This is the fourth most common move, and I want my Chessable peeps to get their opponents out of their prep ASAP, and also play something that is good for Black!   Typically, Black plays either  3...e6  @@StartBracket@@that's what I usually play@@EndBracket@@ or  3...g6  . But since your opponents will be booked to the teeth in those lines, let's make it tough for White right away! }
4. Bxc6
{ White, having played Bb5 last move, decides to capture the knight and double Black's pawns. }
4... dxc6
{ Black always takes with the d-pawn so the c8-bishop can develop normally. }
5. e5 Nd5 { Black's favorite square in the Rossolimo! } 6. h3
{ Preventing ...Bc8-g4. } 6... Bf5
{ Black loves to occupy the d5 and f5-squares with their pieces after White plays e4-e5. }
7. O-O e6 { Time to get our last minor piece out. } 8. d3 Be7
{ Black is doing well here. The most interesting plan is to play ...h7-h5 and ...g7-g5 and attack! More mundane players can just castle kingside, but that's less fun! }
