16. Qg3 Qe7 { Black cannot castle kingside, but there are two ways to castle! }
17. fxe6 fxe6 18. Be2 { Threatening 19. Bh5+. } 18... O-O-O
{ A perfectly cromulent move! } 19. Bg4
{ Putting pressure on Black's e6-pawn. } 19... h5
{ Kicking the bishop and using their isolated pawn to gain space. } 20. Bh3 d4
{ Black keeps making threats. } 21. Ne2 h4 22. Qg4 d3
{ Opening up the h8-a1 diagonal for the f6-bishop. } 23. Rxd3 Rxd3 24. cxd3 Kb8
{ Black's great bishops compensate for their pawn minus. } *

