7. Nde2
{ White usually tries to play Ne2-g3 and saves the b3-square for their c4-bishop. }
7... e6 8. O-O Be7 { Black completes development and has a solid position. } 9.
Bb3 a6
{ Black will castle next move and has a typical Open Sicilian position with their nice center pawns on e6 and d6, and later will play ...b7-b5 after moving their queen off b6. }
