10... g5 11. Bg3 h5 { Black meets aggression with aggression! } 12. h4
{ This stops Black from playing ...h5-h4, trapping the bishop on g3. } 12... g4
13. Qd3 e5
{ Black makes threats every move. Now the g3-bishop is badly placed. } 14. Nf5
{ Knife f5! } 14... Bxf5
{ Chomping off the dangerous knight and giving Black all the center pawns. }
15. exf5 Qb6
{ The position is very complicated, the engine says equal, but both sides have chances. Black can play on the half-open b-file, and has two center pawns to zero, so, I prefer Black. }
