1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4
{ The Grand Prix Attack. Very popular with players under 2200, however, not played at the Super-GM level, except for the occasional blitz or bullet game! }
3... e6
{ This is less common than  3...g6  . It is safer, and it is Kasparov's choice in this variation.   Most of your opponents will be more booked up on 3...g6. }
4. Nf3 d5 { The point of 3...e6. } 5. Bb5
{ Some people only call it the Grand Prix Attack once White plays Bb5, in all variations.  5.e5?!  This may be played by lower rated players, but the engine says Black is already better!  Nh6!  The knight is headed for the f5-square where it's excellently placed.  6.d4  This looks like a French Defense. However, White would prefer to have their d4-pawn defended by the c-pawn, as in the French Advance variation.  6...cxd4  7.Nxd4  White wishes they could play cxd4 to keep their center intact.  7...Bd7  8.Be3  Nxd4  Time to play ...Nf5, but we must get rid of the White d4-knight first.  9.Bxd4  Nf5  The engine says Black is clearly better. Black has easy play with ...Qa5, ...Bb4, ...Rc8, ...O-O. }
5... Ne7
{ This ensures Black will not ruin their pawn structure by backing up their c6-knight with the other knight. }
6. Qe2 { This unusual move has an odd idea of playing Nd1-f2. } 6... d4 7. Nd1
a6 { Black just keeps making threats! } 8. Bxc6+
{ 8.Ba4??  b5  9.Bb3  c4  and Black wins a piece. } 8... Nxc6 9. d3 Be7
{ Black has two bishops, more space on the queenside, and no issues.   Black is already better. }
10. O-O f5
{ The engine loves this move! It's never been played, but it makes the Nd1-f2 maneuver look silly. The f5-pawn controls e4 and g4 where the f2-knight could potentially go.   Now Black can concentrate on the queenside and White has no initiative on the kingside. This move stops White from ever playing f4-f5, so the c1-bishop is not active. }
11. Nf2 O-O
{ Black can play ...b7-b5 and ...Bc8-b7 whereas White has little to do.   Black is clearly better here, and when the position opens up in the center or queenside then Black's advantage will grow due to his two bishops. The white Bishop is sad. }
