4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Bb2 Qe4+ { This rare move basically refutes 5. Bb2. } 6. Ne2
{ 6.Be2!?  Qxg2  7.Bf3  Qg6  Black is ahead two pawns and White has little compensation. Black can just develop their knights and eventually, when they castle kingside they will be winning.   6.Qe2?  Qxc2  wins for Black. }
6... e5 7. axb4 Bxb4
{ The trade on b4 is good for Black, since they get to develop their bishop with the recapture. }
8. Nc3 Bxc3 { This is excellent since the e2-knight is still pinned. } 9. Bxc3
Ne7
{ Black is ahead a pawn for no compensation. Black develops and castles normally and should be winning. }
